           ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <div class="discounts-strip">
        <div class="discounts-strip-head">
          <h2>Discounts &amp; family packages</h2>
          <p>Layer these on top of any package. Multiple discounts can stack.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="discounts-grid">
          <div class="discount-card">
            <div class="discount-pct">−15%</div>
            <div class="discount-title">First-time client</div>
            <div class="discount-desc">First matter with Imverica gets an introductory discount, applied automatically.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="discount-card">
            <div class="discount-pct">−10%</div>
            <div class="discount-title">Family bundle</div>
            <div class="discount-desc">Two or more family members on the same I-130 / I-485 flow — discount on the second relative onward.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="discount-card">
            <div class="discount-pct">−10%</div>
            <div class="discount-title">Multi-form bundle</div>
            <div class="discount-desc">Three or more forms from the same family (e.g. full I-485 package) — discount on the bundle total.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="discount-card">
            <div class="discount-pct">−10%</div>
            <div class="discount-title">Referral credit</div>
            <div class="discount-desc">You refer a new client to Imverica — both of you get a credit on the next invoice.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="discount-card">
            <div class="discount-pct">−25%</div>
            <div class="discount-title">Fee-waiver verified</div>
            <div class="discount-desc">If your household qualifies for the USCIS fee waiver (I-912) or California court fee waiver — we reduce our fee too.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="discount-card discount-card--b2b">
            <div class="discount-pct">B2B</div>
            <div class="discount-title">Attorney retainer</div>
            <div class="discount-desc">Law firms with a monthly retainer (10+ hours/month) bill at our reduced paralegal rate. <a href="/for-attorneys">See attorney pricing →</a></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
           Positioning strip — software vs Imverica vs attorney
           ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <div class="compare-strip">
        <h2>Where we sit in the market</h2>
        <p class="compare-intro">For a sense of value, here's how Imverica compares to two adjacent options — DIY software and a private attorney. We sit in the middle on price, with full multilingual human support, LDA registration, and supervising attorney oversight.</p>
        <div class="compare-grid">
          <div class="compare-col compare-col--software">
            <div class="compare-tier">DIY software</div>
            <div class="compare-name">CitizenPath, LegalZoom</div>
            <ul>
              <li>~$79–$279 per form</li>
              <li>No human review</li>
              <li>English only</li>
              <li>You handle everything</li>
              <li>No LDA / IC registration</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="compare-col compare-col--imverica">
            <div class="compare-tier compare-tier--featured">Imverica</div>
            <div class="compare-name">California LDA + Immigration Consultant</div>
            <ul>
              <li>Flat-fee packages from $149</li>
              <li>Real humans, 4 languages</li>
              <li>Registered, bonded, supervised</li>
              <li>We prepare + assemble + send</li>
              <li>Document preparation only</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="compare-col compare-col--attorney">
            <div class="compare-tier">Private attorney</div>
            <div class="compare-name">Solo / small firm</div>
            <ul>
              <li>$500 – $15,000+ per matter</li>
              <li>Legal advice + strategy</li>
              <li>Court representation</li>
              <li>Hourly creep common</li>
              <li>Needed for litigation, denials, complex strategy</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
           FAQ — small but important
           ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <div class="pricing-faq">
        <h2>Common questions about pricing</h2>
        <details>
          <summary>Are government filing fees included?</summary>
          <p>No. The "Gov. fee*" column shows what you pay <em>directly</em> to USCIS, the court, or the Secretary of State. Imverica's fee is for document preparation. You pay each entity separately — that's a California LDA requirement.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>Is the price really flat, or could it go up later?</summary>
          <p>Flat. Your written engagement agreement locks the price before we start. If your matter turns out more complex than disclosed at intake (criminal history not mentioned, prior denial not disclosed, dependents added), we tell you the add-on price <em>before</em> doing the extra work. You approve, or you walk — no hidden fees.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>Why is asylum "from $1,599" instead of a fixed price?</summary>
          <p>Asylum and removal-defense cases vary enormously. A 22-year-old single asylum applicant with one persecution event is a different document package than a family of five with mixed nationalities and ten years of country-conditions evidence. We quote after reviewing your facts. Final price is in writing before any work starts.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>What does the discount stacking actually look like?</summary>
          <p>Example: full I-485 marriage package ($1,799) for a first-time client (−15%) using a fee waiver (−25%) = $1,169. We show the math on every quote.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>What if I can't afford the listed price?</summary>
          <p>Call <a href="tel:+19163993992">+1 (916) 399-3992</a>. If your household qualifies for a USCIS or court fee waiver, we apply a 25% Imverica discount too. For genuine hardship cases we offer payment plans (50% to start, balance at delivery). Don't walk away because of price — talk to us.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>Do you ever decline a case?</summary>
          <p>Yes. If your matter genuinely needs a lawyer — active litigation, court representation, complex legal strategy, prior denials with appeal deadlines — we say so on the first call and refer you to a licensed immigration attorney we trust. We'd rather lose your case than oversell what an LDA can do.</p>
        </details>
      </div>

      <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
           Big regulatory note at the bottom
           ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <div class="pricing-legal">
        <h3>Important — please read</h3>
        <p>
          All prices above are for <strong>document preparation only</strong>. They are
          quoted in US dollars, exclude government filing fees (USCIS / court / Secretary
          of State / county clerk), and exclude any optional services like mailing,
          translation certification, or attorney review. A written engagement agreement
          locks the final price before any work begins, in your language (English,
          Russian, Ukrainian, or Spanish), per Cal. Bus. &amp; Prof. Code §§6410, 6411
          and §§22441, 22442.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Imverica Legal Solutions is not a law firm.</strong> Imverica is the
          consumer-facing brand of Imverica LLC, a California-registered Legal Document
          Assistant (Cal. Bus. &amp; Prof. Code §§6400–6415) and Immigration Consultant
          (§§22440–22448). We do not give legal advice, do not establish an
          attorney-client relationship, do not represent you in court or before
          USCIS / EOIR, and do not recommend which form you should file. All work is
          performed under the self-represented party's direction. If your situation
          needs legal advice, consult a licensed attorney.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

